HEADWORD: Cambist
<hw>Cam"bist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>cambiste</ets>, It. <ets>cambista</ets>, fr. L. <ets>cambire</ets>
to exchange. See <er>Change</er>.]</ety> <def>A banker; a money changer
or broker; one who deals in bills of exchange, or who is skilled in the
science of exchange.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cambistry</ent>⟦br⟧
